=============================================================================

Outputs

Your README says the validation scripts write to:

outputs/radiating_covariance

outputs/validation

For peer review, keep only small, curated, manuscript-facing outputs:

summary JSON/CSV files, benchmark manifests, selected SVG/PDF/PNG figures.

Ignore large raw arrays, full optimization dumps, caches, and temporary runs.

=============================================================================

outputs/**

Keep output folder readmes/manifests

!outputs/
!outputs//README.md
!outputs//.md
!outputs/**/.json
!outputs//*.csv
!outputs//.txt
!outputs/**/.yaml
!outputs/**/*.yml

Keep publication/review figures

!outputs//*.svg
!outputs//.png
!outputs/**/.pdf

But ignore heavy numerical binary outputs anywhere under outputs

outputs//*.npy
outputs//.npz
outputs/**/.pkl
outputs//*.pickle
outputs//.h5
outputs/**/.hdf5
outputs//*.mat
outputs//.pt
outputs/**/.pth
outputs//*.ckpt
outputs//.parquet
outputs/**/.feather

Ignore likely raw optimization/campaign dumps

outputs//raw/
outputs//raw_results/
outputs//raw_outputs/
outputs//checkpoints/
outputs//population*
outputs//generations/
outputs//full_runs/
outputs//debug/
outputs//tmp/
outputs//temp/

